e, United Kingdom","Medhope, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rowton, Shropshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Gisburne, Craven, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Gisburn, Yorkshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Barnoldswick, Lancashire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1410–16 April 1483":"1410–16. april 1483","1410–1483":"1410–1483","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1434–1467":"1434–1467","1385–Male":"1385–Afdød","1387–Female":"1387–Afdød","16 April 1483":"16. april 1483","1434":"1434","1467":"1467","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","about 1432":"omkring 1432","Yorkshire, England":"Jórvík, England, United Kingdom","Whalley, Ribble Valley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Whalley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Medhope, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Jórvík, England, United Kingdom","Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Gisburne, Craven, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Gisburn, Jórvík, England, United Kingdom","Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1410–16 April 1483":"1410–16 april 1483","1410–1483":"1410–1483","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1434–1467":"1434–1467","1385–Male":"1385–Overleden","1387–Female":"1387–Overleden","16 April 1483":"16 april 1483","1434":"1434","1467":"1467","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","about 1432":"circa 1432","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Whalley, Ribble Valley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Whalley, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Medhope, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rowton, Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Gisburne, Craven, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Gisburn, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Barnoldswick, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1410–16 April 1483":"1410–16 April 1483","1410–1483":"1410–1483","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1434–1467":"1434–1467","1385–Male":"1385–Deceased","1387–Female":"1387–Deceased","16 April 1483":"16 April 1483","1434":"1434","1467":"1467","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","about 1432":"about 1432","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Whalley, Ribble Valley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Whalley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Medhope, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Gisburne, Craven, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Gisburn, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bannister","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from Old French <i>banaste</i>, <i>banastre</i> ‘covering for a cart or wagon; basket’, i.e. a large wicker container. In the 12th century a Norman family of this name had estates in Orne, Normandy, and in England. Ricardus <i>Banastre</i> appears in charters relating to the Earls of Chester <i>c.</i> 1120–29. With what sense the Norman surname was acquired is unknown. It can hardly have been occupational, contrary to Reaney's view that it denoted a basket maker. It is possible that many or even all of the later bearers of the surname were descended from this knightly family. However, several men with this surname in the 14th-century Poll Tax Returns are described as servants or agricultural laborers, while Ricardus <i>Banastr'</i>, recorded in 1381 was a butcher. It is conceivable that these men took their name from Middle English <i>banastre</i>, a borrowing of the French word, and that it referred to a basket or hamper they used in their work. Alternatively, they may have belonged to branches of the knightly family that had fallen in the social scale. The term denoting a stair rail is unconnected with this name; it was not used before the 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Banister","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Bannister  .","History: The naturalist John Banister (1650–92) was born in Gloucestershire, England, and came to VA in 1678."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ellen Bannister was born in 1410, in Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Richard Bannister, was 25 and her mother, Catharine BOLTON, was 24. She married Laurence Lister about 1432, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 16 April 1483, in Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1410–16 April 1483":"1410–16. aprill 1483","1410–1483":"1410–1483","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1434–1467":"1434–1467","1385–Male":"1385–Surnud","1387–Female":"1387–Surnud","16 April 1483":"16. aprill 1483","1434":"1434","1467":"1467","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","about 1432":"umbes 1432","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whalley, Ribble Valley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Whalley, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Medhope, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rowton, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gisburne, Craven, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Gisburn, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Barnoldswick, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1410–16 April 1483":"1410–16. huhtikuuta 1483","1410–1483":"1410–1483","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1434–1467":"1434–1467","1385–Male":"1385–Kuollut","1387–Female":"1387–Kuollut","16 April 1483":"16. huhtikuuta 1483","1434":"1434","1467":"1467","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","about 1432":"noin 1432","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Whalley, Ribble Valley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Whalley, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Medhope, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rowton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Rowton, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gisburne, Craven, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Gisburn, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barnoldswick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Barnoldswick, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1410–16 April 1483":"1410–16 avril 1483","1410–1483":"1410–1483","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1434–1467":"1434–1467","1385–Male":"1385–Décédé","13